node.text:
Climate change and protecting the environment are super close to my heart. Yet when I read the latest news and research, I feel overwhelmed, anxious and sad. 

Lots of us feel this way. And climate change - especially the inaction of people in power - is driving an epidemic of mental health problems. “Eco-anxiety” is on the rise, and young people are some of the worst affected. 

So, I asked my friend @cloverhogan from @forceofnature.xyz to tell us more about eco-anxiety - what it is, how to deal with these feelings, and how to become a force for change. Check it out 🌎  and drop any other questions you have on climate change and mental health below ⬇️ #ecoanxiety #climatechange #climatecrisis #youarenotalone

node.text:
🖤Featuring Sophie’s poem tonight @sophiesylin 

hi, my name is Sophie and i am a Senior in Girl Scouts. for my journey this year, i chose Girltopia - a journey where girls embark on a mission towards an ideal world for girls. to me, Girltopia is a world in which girls are accepted, respected, and treated as equals, and are able to go about their lives without feeling judged, uncomfortable, or simply “not enough.” for my journey project i chose to write a poem which touches on the internal struggles that girls (or anyone) may face. through this poem i hoped to spread the message that you are never alone. that although it may not feel like it, there is someone out there who understands what you’re going through and who wants to help you on your journey of growth. what you are going through is real and may feel impossible to overcome. but know there is a God who loves you unconditionally and wholeheartedly. know that there are people who care for you and want to support you the whole way. know that you are strong and capable of overcoming your obstacles. know that i stand with you.

if you are in need of help or just need someone to talk to, you can always text “HELLO” to 741741 (Crisis Text Line)

or you can always call 1-800-273-8255 (National Suicide Prevention Lifeline) 

remember: you are beautiful, you are loved, your life matters ♥︎ keep flying
#girlscouts #journey #girltopia #peom #birds #crisistextline

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021 tagging @sophiesylin. May be an image of text that says 'There once was a little bird, filled with sunshine and happiness and warmth. She was little bundle ofjoy who spread warmth and laughter every everywhere she went. Her heart knew no bounds and she was 80 carefree, 80 confident, so kind. But then she learned of the nature of the world she lived in, filled with sin, and hate, and greed, and misunderstanding. Experiences and stories altered her naïve perspective. And she saw things for what they are.'.

Photo by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'She began to trust others less and less and had doubts. Her feathers easily ruffled and slowly being plucked one by one by her own beak. Instances ofbeauty were rare, short, and sweet. A storm came bringing all of its darkness and rain with it. She saw how other craved understanding and just wanted to be understood. She saw things that yanked on her heartstrings and she wanted to help, felt she needed to help, that she had to help... But how could she? When she was already drowning in her own loneliness and sorrows.'.

Photo by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Her fellow birds became her closest family. But she knew she couldn't burden them with all her troubles. In her own nest, she was considered an outsider: different, problematic, issues that made her a problem That she was making every hing up. For what, attention? an excuse? She realized she had no one. That she was alone.'.

Photo by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'She didn't know who she was or what she was meant to be or even why the hell this was happening. She tried distract herself by focusing on others on other people's stories on routine and habits. And by putting up mask ofhappiness and joy each day 80 others couldn't see the pain. While night she silently wept until sleep came. She felt trapped in never ending whirlpool ofher own tears and misery and hopelessnes8. Desperate for a way out.'.

Photo by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'And then it made her think ofall the other birds in the world, who were feeling the same. Ugly, unsure, useless. And although she still had her own struggles, she knew that no one else deserved to feel this way. So she dedicated her life To helping them understand themselves To showing them That they matter That they are not alone That they are beautiful. That they are loved.'.

Photo by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'And through this process She began to understand herself. And no longer felt the need To cover herself with mask. She learned to embrace her flaws to open up and share ofher own battles. That her battles are what made her stronger more empathetic more hopeful. She learned to forgive those who wronged her. And love them. She learned fjustice and mercy But above all, grace. Until one day She turned to embers. Only to emerge days later from the ash and dust,'.
Photo by Cally Tate on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A Phoenix'.

node.text:
Stop talking yourself out of opportunities!!!! 

I couldn't tell you how many times I've doubted myself and backed out of something. Whether it was big or small. To be honest, that's a trait of mine I don't exactly like. But we can change. We can practice trying to new things. We can help rewrite ourselves to become the best version possible. 

#opportunity #selftalk #opportunities #opportunist #talktoyourself #growing #selfdoubt

Here are many different versions of the same picture because I could not for the life of me pick one. And yes the first two are different colors, 1st is white, 2nd is more of a cream color lol. 

Anyways, there are always things or people saying you deserve this and that. You do deserve happiness and love. But deserve does not equal entitlement. Deserve in this case means it should be there, and if it's not then something needs to change. 

#youareloved #beautiful #youdeservelove #entitlement #mentalhealth #floraldesign #selflove #spreadlove

node.text:
In the end, you are the only person that will always be with you. So you need to learn how to be okay with just yourself. To be able to just be with your mind and not break down. It's okay if that happens to you, but the goal is to get where that doesn't happen. But it takes work to make improvements. As hard as it is you just have to try. Little by little every day. One new self-helping action a day can set you up for success. 
Trying new things for self-growth can be uncomfortable and maybe even embarrassing. 
🤍You just have to remember, there's nothing to be embarrassed about if all you're doing is trying to be better. 

#watchyourself #watchyourback #youareenough #selfhelp #selfcare #goodhabits #goodhabitsforlife #mentalhealthadvocate #tips #explore #quotes #passion

node.text:
I’m glad to see you here 🤎

Reach out and find what makes you YOU. Grab ahold of the things that make you grow and give you happiness. We spend so much time doing things we don’t even like doing, so start spending some time doing thing that you actually like. Be productive, get up and start. I know it’s easier said than done but all you need to do is take the first step. 

#nature #mushrooms #hippiestyle #mentalhealth #youareloved #happiness #peace #peaceofmind #mindfulness #spiritual

node.text:
Good morning!! 
The energy you create for yourself will carry you through today. You get to decide what that energy says and attracts. 

So, trauma, it sucks and it can sometimes always stick with us. But the more you work on resolving the past memories and emotions the better you will feel. For me therapy was the way to do this and it could be yours too. But that doesn’t mean you can’t try some other healthy coping mechanism. 

#traumabonding #traumahealing #traumaresponse #traumarecovery #trauma #traumatherapy #therapy #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthquotes #depression #ptsd #youareloved

node.text:
I came across this post a few minutes ago and immediately LOVED IT! So I figured why not repost it? I haven’t posted someone else’s work in a while, so why not? 

This is absolutely correct, at least for myself. I can’t speak for you. But I hope one day you start healing for yourself and learn things like this too. 

Grieving can be healthy. When we get better we can often grieve our past selves and what we left behind. But what we leave behind is meant for the past. Our new selves flourish in learning and accepting environments. 

Picture Credits: @jumponborderline 

#bpd #depression #anxiety #grieving #grief #griefquotes #healing #healingjourney #griefjourney #therapy #getbettertoday #youarenotalone

node.text:
Suicide means something different to everyone. 
However, it should not indicate someone is just craving attention. Even if they were, committing suicide shows there is a much deeper problem that they were facing. 
People should not grow up believing that wanting to die is completely normal and doesn't need to be brought up. We shouldn’t have to live our lives waiting for it to end. Life is meant for living. 

#suicideprevention #suicideawarness #suicide #suicidehotline #suicidememeshelpmeovercomemyfearofactuallydyingbymakinglightheartedjokes #suicideisnottheanswer #depression #mentalillness #anxiety #trauma #selfish  #poverty #guilt #stophomophobia
